   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Before starting the work instruction activity, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol id="substeps_v24_fg5_tcc">
               <li>
                  <p>Do not begin these tasks without confirmation that personnel directly
                     involved have completed the required training associated with the work
                     instruction activity and have reviewed this document.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Gather necessary tools and equipment as identified below in the Equipment
                     Section.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Wear and use additional Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) and safety
                     equipment required for this specific work instruction.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Obey all applicable safety requirements and procedures.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Notify appropriate personnel of the activity and estimated time needed to
                     complete the tasks.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Follow all Lockout/Tagout procedures when work instruction activity requires
                     isolating energy in the designated area. Verify energy is isolated before
                     starting work.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Prior to the Job Change or FTA setup, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol id="substeps_nwt_mg5_tcc">
               <li>
                  <p>Monitor the production flow to ensure that the machine is properly set up in
                     accordance with the appropriate Container Handling Work Instruction:</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_jvt_ng5_tcc">
                        <li>INS-03-013 (FP without Plug Gauge)</li>
                        <li>INS-03-014 (FPX)</li>
                        <li>INS-03-015 (FPX2)</li>
                        <li>INS-03-018 (FP with Plug Gauge)</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_bg1_nh5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image1.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_cg1_nh5_tcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To set up the Headplate, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol id="substeps_id4_th5_tcc">
               <li>
                  <p>Jog a commercial quality container of the type to be inspected into station
                     #1 of the machine.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_o2p_vh5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_p2p_vh5_tcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Verify the gauge light is on.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Confirm the headplate height adjustment in accordance with the appropriate
                     Container Handling Work Instruction:</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_ig2_zh5_tcc">
                        <li>INS-03-013 (FP without Plug Gauge)</li>
                        <li>INS-03-014 (FPX)</li>
                        <li>INS-03-015 (FPX2)</li>
                        <li>INS-03-018 (FP with Plug Gauge)</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_pxx_235_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image4.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_qxx_235_tcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>For the mechanical setup of the FTA Head Assembly, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol id="substeps_qb4_r35_tcc">
               <li>
                  <p>Select <uicontrol>Display &gt; FTA</uicontrol> from the IPS Main Menu.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_nzf_hk5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image5.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_ozf_hk5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Select <uicontrol>Image &gt; Scope</uicontrol> from the FTA Main Menu to display
                     the Scope Screen.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <image href="media/image6.jpg"
                               placement="break"
                               id="image_yn4_kk5_tcc"
                               align="center"
                               scale="50"/>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Press the <uicontrol>Scope On</uicontrol> button.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_tbg_v35_tcc">
                        <li>Enable the Cross Hairs to aid in setup.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_isr_r1v_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image7.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_t44_sk5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>If the container is not appearing on the screen, use the up / down and in /
                     out adjustments until an image appears.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_zrh_z35_tcc">
                        <li>Locking Screws (up / down)</li>
                        <li> Adjustment Screw (up / down)</li>
                        <li>Locking Screws (in / out) (recessed)</li>
                        <li>Adjustment Knob (in / out)</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_f1h_xk5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image8.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_g1h_xk5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>While monitoring the Scope Screen, slightly loosen the Locking Screw and
                     adjust the position of the Head Assembly left/right using the Adjustment Screw
                     until the sealing surface image is horizontal as in the image shown. When
                     finished, tighten the Locking Screw.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_jcg_fj5_tcc">
                        <li>Locking Screw (left / right)</li>
                        <li>Adjustment Screw (left / right)</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_xp3_cl5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image9.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_yp3_cl5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>While monitoring the Scope Screen, loosen the Locking Screws (recessed) and
                     adjust the position of the Head Assembly in/out using the Adjustment Knob until
                     the sealing surface image is vertically centered as in the image shown. When
                     finished, tighten the Locking Screws.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_xqx_jj5_tcc">
                        <li>Locking Screws (in / out)</li>
                        <li>Adjustment Knob (in / out)</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_tjx_fl5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image10.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_ujx_fl5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>While monitoring the Scope Screen, slightly loosen the Locking Screws and
                     adjust the position of the Head Assembly up/down using the Adjustment Screw
                     until the vertical Wire Edge laser line is centered as in the image shown. When
                     finished, tighten the Locking Screws.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_c5l_4j5_tcc">
                        <li>Locking Screws (up / down)</li>
                        <li>Adjustment Screw (up / down)</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_w3b_kl5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image11.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_x3b_kl5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>When the laser is centered on the crosshairs, confirm that the sealing
                     surface of the container is in focus. If it is not, the FTA Head requires
                     realignment or repair.</p>
                  <p>
                     <note id="note_lx2_ml5_tcc">
                        <p>The adjustment steps above may need to be repeated until the image is
                           centered on the crosshairs.</p>
                     </note>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_d4g_4l5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image12.jpg" id="image_e4g_4l5_tcc" placement="inline"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To adjust the FTA light settings, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol id="substeps_ull_nn5_tcc">
               <li>
                  <p>Adjust the Sealing Surface Balanceslider to obtain an even contrast
                     throughout the image from top to bottom.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_uxq_yn5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image13.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_vxq_yn5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                        <fig id="fig_vj4_zn5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image14.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_wj4_zn5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Adjust the Sealing Surface Intensity slider until the Measured SS
                     Intensity reads between 80 and 90.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_xfn_145_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image15.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_yfn_145_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Adjust the Laser Intensityslider until the Measured WE Width indicates
                     “Good.”</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_t3f_rn5_tcc">
                        <li>The ideal WE Width is 4.0.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_i25_b45_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image16.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_j25_b45_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                        <fig id="fig_cy5_245_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image17.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_dy5_245_tcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>For the software setup of the FTA, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol id="substeps_ely_m45_tcc">
               <li>
                  <p>Select <uicontrol>Image&gt;Trap</uicontrol>.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_nm1_wq5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image18.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_om1_wq5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Press the <uicontrol>Set Trap</uicontrol> button.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_nfc_zq5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image19.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_ofc_zq5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>When the “Waiting” message appears, run one commercial quality container
                     through the machine.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_ax2_br5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image20.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_bx2_br5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>When the “Trapped” message appears, press the <uicontrol>View</uicontrol>
                     button corresponding to the machine being set up.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_cbz_cr5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image21.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_dbz_cr5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Press the <uicontrol>Setup</uicontrol> button.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_ywm_r45_tcc">
                        <li>When the confirmation popup appears that states the changes made in this
                           screen will affect the calculated image only, press the
                              <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol> button.</li>
                        <li>The Job Change and Sensitivity buttons will now display
                           along the right side of the screen.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_z1s_fr5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image22.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_abs_fr5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                        <fig id="fig_s25_gs5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image23.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_t25_gs5_tcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Press the <uicontrol>Job Change &gt; Job Setup</uicontrol> button in the Job
                     Change popup menu to display the Job Setup Screen.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_jyv_3s5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image24.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_kyv_3s5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Verify that theBottle Type is set toNormal.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_zkz_v45_tcc">
                        <li>Selecting the Bottle Type will reset all the FTA settings to
                           their default values.</li>
                        <li>Choose the proper type of finish as needed.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_igr_ls5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image25.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_jgr_ls5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Press the <uicontrol>Finish Diameter</uicontrol> button corresponding to the
                     active FP and use the numeric keypad popup to specify the container’s finish
                     diameter.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_ysd_y45_tcc">
                        <li>The value must be entered in millimeters even if the system is not set
                           to metric.</li>
                        <li>Wide angle lens should not be used on standard finishes. If a wide angle
                           lens is used, set the finish diameter as follows:<ol id="ol_ulq_z45_tcc">
                              <li>Less than 50 millimeters, set the value to 70% of the actual
                                 diameter.</li>
                              <li>More than 50 millimeters, set the value to 35 millimeters.</li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_zyk_rq5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image26.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_azk_rq5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                        <fig id="fig_bzk_rq5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image27.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_czk_rq5_tcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Select an individual frame to maximize it on the View Image Screen.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Press the <uicontrol>Job Change &gt; Finish Learn</uicontrol> button in the Job
                     Change popup menu.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Select the top of the finish in the image center as prompted.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Select the bottom of the finish in the image center as prompted.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>When the informational popup appears stating the new Finish Width and initial
                     Finish Intensity, press the <uicontrol>Yes</uicontrol> button.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Press the <uicontrol>Save Changes</uicontrol> button beneath the “Unsaved
                     Changes” heading. Press the <uicontrol>Yes</uicontrol> button when the confirm
                     popup appears.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Verify the appropriate inspection channels are enabled according to the FTA
                     section of MSDR INS-03-030 Minimum Inspection Channels on Soul Equipment.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Verify the inspection channel settings are within the ranges specified in the
                     FTA section of MSDR INS-07-031 Inspection Device Setup Parameters for Soul
                     Equipment.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Validate the device based on Work Instruction INS-03-011 Equipment Validation
                     Process – Inspection Device.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To fine tune the mechanical setup of the FTA Head Assembly as needed, perform the
               following steps:</p>
            <ol id="substeps_ffn_3t5_tcc">
               <li>
                  <p>Press <uicontrol>Status &gt; Pockets</uicontrol> to display the FTA Pocket
                     Screen.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_mct_c55_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image34.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_nct_c55_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Clear out all the totals by pressing the <uicontrol>Clear</uicontrol>
                     button.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_wlj_255_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image35.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_xlj_255_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Start the machine (ensure production ware is available at the infeed).</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_acv_lt5_tcc">
                        <li>The numbers shown in the lower left are the values obtained for the
                           individual pockets of each machine and an average for all the
                           pockets.</li>
                        <li>The numbers shown in the upper left are the minimum / maximum values
                           obtained during the 15 minute inspection interval.</li>
                        <li>As the containers travel through the pockets, each gray number will turn
                           black, yellow, or red when a sufficient number of containers have
                           passed.</li>
                        <li>The numbers will display black when acceptable, yellow when approaching
                           a limit, or red when the limit has been exceeded. The FTA Head is
                           properly adjusted when all these numbers are black.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_rnj_g55_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image36.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_snj_g55_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                        <fig id="fig_gdr_355_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image37.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_hdr_355_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Note the pocket values for each machine. If the values are displayed in
                     yellow or red, perform steps 5 through 9. If this does not result in the values
                     turning black (acceptable), the container handling must be reviewed.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Press the <uicontrol>Adjust</uicontrol> button corresponding to the machine
                     needing adjustment. This will display a list of specific adjustments that can
                     be made to improve the average pocket location.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_iwz_l55_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image38.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_jwz_l55_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Adjust the FTA Head according to the instructions in the Adjust Head
                     popup.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ol id="ol_qkc_5t5_tcc">
                        <li>Continue to monitor the values and perform additional adjustments of the
                           FTA Head until the percentages associated with each of the three Head
                           Adjustments are as close to zero as possible.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_pjj_455_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image39.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_qjj_455_tcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Use the “First 10” option in the Trap screen to obtain multiple trapped
                     images. </p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_knl_5y5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image40.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_lnl_5y5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Press the <uicontrol>Set Trap</uicontrol> button.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_ilr_wy5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image41.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_jlr_wy5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Review each image to ensure that the finish is properly centered.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_agm_bz5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image42.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_bgm_bz5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  scale="50"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To verify the consistency of the Initial Intensity values (once all the machines on the line are set up), perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol id="substeps_eq2_nz5_tcc">
               <li>
                  <p>Select <uicontrol>Setup &gt; Job Change &gt; Finish Intensity</uicontrol> to
                     display the Initial Intensity Screen.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_rt1_5z5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image43.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_st1_5z5_tcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Verify the Initial Intensity values are within ±5 for all the machines. If
                     any of the values are outside of this range, perform Work Instruction
                     INS-03-030 Finish Setup - Soul - FTA Intensity Balance.</p>
                  <p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_plk_vz5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image44.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_qlk_vz5_tcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <note id="note_hlx_qz5_tcc">
                        <p>If any of the Initial Intensity values are significantly lower than other
                           values on the line, (70 in the above example), and the Sealing Surface
                           Intensity value must be adjusted to near 100 to obtain the desired
                           measured intensity, this may indicate that the FTA Head needs
                           servicing.</p>
                     </note>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_tzp_wz5_tcc">
                           <image href="media/image45.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_uzp_wz5_tcc"
                                  align="center"
